The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Mahindra coach likely to be axed
                                                   Mahindra coach likely to be axed
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: The city football clubs, notorious for their habit of changing coaches, seem to be the decided lot this time with quite a few I-League clubs mulling a change at the helm before the start of the new season.         
	Mohun Bagan, East Bengal and United SC  the three Calcutta clubs in next seasons I-league  would continue with their coaches from last season.         
	But Mumbai clubs Mahindra United and Mumbai FC are set to dump their coaches. Mahindras Derrick Pereira is likely to get the axe and a decision in that regard will be taken at the club meeting on Thursday. The future of Mumbai FCs British coach David Booth also looks dim.         
	I-League champions Churchill Brothers are yet to decide whether they want to retain Serbian coach Zoran Djordjevic for the next season. Incidentally, world governing body Fifa has congratulated Churchill Brothers for their maiden I-League title.         
	Meanwhile, Mohun Bagan have struck a deal with Mumbai FC footballers K. Kulothungan and Riston Rodrigues for the next season.         
	East Bengal are unlikely to land the services of Brazilian midfielder Beto. The footballer has a contract with Dempo for the next season and is unlikely to get a release.                                                                                                                       
